<a name="skipmaincontent"></a><h1 class="bac">Public Finance Summer Associate</h1>
<h2 class="bac">Our Business</h2>
<p class="bac">
Bank of America Securities Public Finance is one of the top municipal underwriters nationally.  Organized by region and specialty, our Investment Bankers are dedicated to understanding the unique operating environments of our clients, and to building strong, enduring client relationships. We are organized into 6 regional and 8 specialty teams.  Regional teams cover state and local governments across the United States; specialty teams cover tax exempt financing for economic development, energy, healthcare, higher education, housing, not-for-profit organizations, student loans, tax-exempt corporate, transportation and water and sewer.  
</p>
<p class="bac">
As a leader in tax exempt financing, our Public Finance team delivers creative solutions for issuers and investors across a range of municipal debt offerings and associated products including:  municipal bonds, taxable, fixed, floating, and auction rate securities, short term financing, reinvestment of bond proceeds and interest rate risk management. The Banc of America Securities Public Finance Group is a fully integrated team of specialists dedicated to helping clients to structure and issue tax exempt debt.
</p>
<p class="bac">
What’s our strategy for success? It starts and ends with serving our clients the solutions and execution they need in today’s market.  Our investment bankers work closely with commercial bankers, sales, trading and underwriting to develop strategic solutions for our clients, leveraging the full power of Bank of America’s franchise.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview</h2>
<p class="bac">
As an active team member focused on a region or specialty area, associates help orchestrate capital raising and strategic advisory transactions.  Associates are called on to:  
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Develop and manage financial models</li>
	<li>Create various financial analyses, based on product and market dynamics</li>
	<li>Perform comprehensive and in-depth company and industry research</li>
	<li>Prepare presentation and other materials for clients</li>
	<li>Participate in due diligence sessions and client meetings</li>
	<li>Interact with deal team members and clients</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications</h2>
<p class="bac">
Candidates must demonstrate a combination of academic aptitude, quantitative skills, computer skills, strategic and creative thinking and distinguished written and oral communications skills. Associates are required to manage several projects at once and work effectively as an individual and as part of a team. Some common driving characteristics we look for:  assertiveness, attention to detail, exceptional academic achievement, initiative, team focus, leadership, self-confidence, strategic and creative thinking capabilities, strong work ethic, and strong communication skills. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Summer Associate Program
<p class="bac">
Summer Associates work in New York and Charlotte.  Offers are made for a specific office and specific industry or product group, based on candidate preference and business need. The summer program kicks off with an orientation session where you'll learn some Bank of America’s basics: technical skills, our views on the markets and professional practices that will make your summer experience all the more valuable.  Training will continue throughout the summer as you participate in presentations and other group and individual projects led by industry experts.  Outstanding performers may be considered for a full-time position upon graduation.
</p>



<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

